    ) VALUES (1409041, 'Diazepam', 'Raloxifene', 'Minor', 'Raloxifene is more than 95% protein bound. Caution should be exercised if raloxifene is coadministered with other highly protein-bound drugs. The mechanism is displacement of the drug from its protein-binding site by raloxifene. Displacement may lead to increased free plasma concentrations and potentiate toxicity of drugs affected by raloxifene. Formal in-vitro studies indicate that raloxifene did not affect the binding of warfarin, phenytoin, or tamoxifen. The clinician may want to use caution when raloxifene is used with other highly-protein bound drugs, such as diazepam, diazoxide, or lidocaine.', NULL, '-', NULL, '-', 'Distribution', NULL, NULL, 'Minor', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317476);
